            "body": "<p>I had a similar problem with a SOAP response I solved it by importing the following maven library<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;! - https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.sun.org.apache/jaxp-ri -&gt;\n         &lt;dependency&gt;\n             &lt;groupId&gt;com.sun.org.apache&lt;/groupId&gt;\n             &lt;artifactId&gt;jaxp-ri&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n             &lt;version&gt;1.4&lt;/version&gt;\n         &lt;/dependency&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>and in the class where I had to receive the answer amount:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>import com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.dom.DocumentImpl;\nimport com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.dom.ElementNSImpl;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>and perform the casting in the following way<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>SERVICEDISPATCHERRESPONSE response;\nDocumentImpl document = (DocumentImpl) ((ElementNSImpl) response.getAny()).GetOwnerDocument();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
